Flyim Privacy Policy
Effective Date: January 01, 2024
Preamble:
Cropim OÜ (hereinafter referred to as “Company,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) manages the Flyim mobile application (hereafter referred to as the “Service”). This Privacy Policy details our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when users (referred to as “you” or “your”) engage with the Service, and outlines the rights and choices associated with said data. By accessing or using the Service, you consent to the data practices described in this policy, in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
I. Collection and Use of Information
Personal Data:
Definition: Personal data, which is information that can be used to identify you, may be collected when you use our Service.
Types: This includes, but is not limited to, User Location (for local weather and wind information) and User Email (for access to drone map features).
Usage Data:
Definition: Information automatically sent by your device related to your use of the Service.
Details: This may encompass your device’s Internet Protocol (IP) address, app and device type and version, Service pages visited, visit timings, and diagnostic data.
Analytics Data:
Usage: Utilizing tools like Crashlytics for collecting app crash logs to enhance Service functionality.
II. Purpose of Data Use
The collected data is utilized for various purposes:
Delivering tailored weather data and no-fly zone information.
Enabling submission and viewing of drone flying sites.
Service modifications notifications.
Customer support and analysis for app improvement.
Monitoring app usage, detecting, and resolving technical issues.
Providing opt-out marketing communications.
III. Data Transfer and Disclosure
Transfer of Data:
International Transfer: Personal Data may be transferred to, and maintained on, computers outside your jurisdiction.
Consent: Your submission of data signifies consent to this transfer.
Security Measures: We commit to ensuring your data’s secure and compliant treatment.
Disclosure for Legal Reasons:
Circumstances: Disclosure may occur to comply with legal obligations, protect our rights or property, prevent Service misuse, ensure public safety, or prevent legal liabilities.
IV. Data Security
While we strive for the secure transmission and storage of your data, absolute security cannot be guaranteed.
V. Third-Party Service Providers
These entities may have access to your Personal Data solely for performing tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for other purposes.
VI. External Links
Our Service may contain links to external sites, over which we have no control and assume no responsibility.
VII. Children’s Privacy
Our Service is not directed at individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect Personal Data from this demographic.
VIII. Compliance with GDPR
In accordance with the GDPR, we take strict measures to protect the privacy and rights of our users. This includes:
Ensuring lawful, fair, and transparent processing of personal data.
Limiting data processing to specific, legitimate purposes.
Minimizing the amount of personal data collected.
Ensuring accuracy of data.
Limiting storage of data to necessary periods.
Guaranteeing integrity, confidentiality, and availability of data.
IX. User Rights under GDPR
As a user of our Service within the scope of GDPR, you are entitled to certain rights, including:
Access to your personal data.
Rectification of inaccurate data.
Erasure of your data (“right to be forgotten”).
Restriction of data processing.
Data portability.
Objection to data processing.
Withdrawal of consent.
Lodging a complaint with a supervisory authority.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at info@cropim.com.
X. Policy Amendments
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. We will notify you of any changes through various channels, including email.
XI. Contact Information
For queries regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us via email at info@cropim.com.
Corporate Information:
